The paper deals with a graph-based data clustering problem, which is a common topic in computer science. The use of forbidden induced subgraphs to characterize the goal graphs suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The focus on kernelization and data reduction rules suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the use of approximation algorithms and running time analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
